My boss gave me an assignment to learn and implement Airbnb's open-source tool, Airflow at our company. Airflow is a data orchestration tool that allows you to programmtically schedule jobs in order to extract, transform, or load data. I was able to successfully implement Airflow and taught my teammates all the interesting things (including Airflow, Docker, Kubernetes, and MORE) I had learned! Here's just a taste of my material :) I had a lot of fun organizing, documenting, and sharing knowledge in a fun and understandable way. Also, my slides are really cute ^^

Day 2: Intro to Airflow and Graph Data Structures
